---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Let's Skate Foundation is the 501(c)(3) nonprofit that runs Elmbrook Speedskating, the nation's first school-district speed skating club."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="sec-inner page-hero">
      <div class="label"><span class="label-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Who we are</div>
      <h1 class="heading">About Let's Skate Foundation</h1>
      <p class="body-text page-lede">
        Let's Skate Foundation is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit empowering youth
        through inclusive access to speed skating by partnering with school
        districts to build community and opportunity.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="sec-inner about-body">
      <h2 class="heading-sm">Our story</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Through our partnership with the Elmbrook School District over the
        past four years, we have taught over three hundred kids how to
        skate and elevated ten skaters to the national level in short and
        long track competition. Today, the program we run —
        <strong>Elmbrook Speedskating</strong> — is the first and only
        school-district speed skating club in the entire nation.
      </p>

      <h2 class="heading-sm">Why two names?</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        <strong>Let's Skate Foundation</strong> is the 501(c)(3) — the
        nonprofit legal entity. <strong>Elmbrook Speedskating</strong> is
        the program we run on the ground, in partnership with the
        Elmbrook School District. When you register to skate, you're
        signing up with the club. When you donate, you're giving to the
        foundation. Two names, one team, one mission.
      </p>

      <h2 class="heading-sm">Get involved</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Whether you want to skate, volunteer, sponsor a kid, or chip in
        $25 — there's a place for you. Email
        <a href="mailto:admin@letsskate.org">admin@letsskate.org</a>
        and we'll find the right way to plug you in.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero { text-align: center; padding-bottom: 2rem; }
  .page-hero .label { justify-content: center; }
  .page-hero h1.heading { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4vw, 3rem); }
  .page-lede { max-width: 640px; margin: 1rem auto 0; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .about-body { max-width: 720px; }
  .heading-sm {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--dark);
  }
  .body-text strong { color: var(--dark); }
  .body-text a { color: var(--teal); font-weight: 700; }
</style>
